  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>17</Version>
    <Date>9/1/2021</Date>
    <Description>Per request from Ali Khan, CSM Diagnostic Domain Lead, made the following updates to support CR#:2204550 within the GIS641_DiagnosticCalDef_GlobalB.caldef file: Added the following 2 new cals: (1) DTC_MASK_U1610_00 (Note: Also removed equivalent old DTC_MASK_U160F_00 cal from the Cal Database since this cal is being replaced by this DTC_MASK_U1610_00 cal) and (2) DTC_MASK_ U1650_00 (Note: Also removed equivalent old DTC_MASK_U0155_00 cal from the Cal Database since this cal is being replaced by this DTC_MASK_U1650_00 cal).</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>18</Version>
    <Date>9/17/2021</Date>
    <Description>Per request from GM Sustain team,  updated the GIS641_DiagnosticCalDef_GlobalB.caldef file to add back in&#xa0;the DTC_MASK_U160F_00&#xa0;and&#xa0;DTC_MASK_U0155_00 calibrations that were removed in the Info3.7/3.8 Cal DB v7.0.5 release. The GM Sustain team confirmed both of these calibrations are still needed for Info3.7 to support the U160F_00&#xa0; and U0155_00 DTCs that are still in the GB_ODX_22.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>19</Version>
    <Date>4/19/2023</Date>
    <Description>Per CR# 3246661 adding new cals DTC_MASK_U018B_00</Description>
    <Author>Andrea Campbell</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefinition Description="U018B00 Lost Communication with Virtual Key Module" Name="DTC_MASK_U018B_00" References="GIS-641, GIS-657" Usage="MID,HIGH,GLOBALB">
    <CalID>_eMUEQN7DEe2Q5N94dNnwHA</CalID>
    <Type>Boolean</Type>
    <Version>3</Version>
