  <CalDefinition Description="Radio System Programming Failure. Upon notification by the handler that the associated supervised signal has failed supervision (typically 2.5 times the nominal periodic rate of the monitored signal). An adjustable debounce time, i.e. X of Y strategy, is permitted at the time that notification of failed supervision has been received by the application to delay storing of the DTC." Name="DTC_MASK_B19B1_50" References="GIS-641" Usage="MID,HIGH,GLOBALB,VCU">
